\begin_layout Theorem*
\begin_inset Argument 1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\emph on
The 
\emph default
Bang-Bang
\emph on
 principle
\end_layout

\end_inset

Let 
\begin_inset Formula $C\subset\mathbb{R}^{m}$
\end_inset

 be a convex compact (of allowed control values).
 For the system 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\dot{x} & =A(t)x(t)+B(t)u(t)\\
x(0) & =\vec{0}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

 every point accessible with 
\bar under
some
\bar default
 control 
\begin_inset Formula $u:I\to C$
\end_inset

 in time 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 is accessible with an 
\bar under
extremal
\bar default
 control 
\begin_inset Formula ${u^{0}:I\to\Ext C}$
\end_inset

 as well.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We won't prove it in full generality, but only in the special case when
 the allowed control values form the unit ball (Holmes) or a 
\emph on
simplex
\emph default
 (Hermes).
\end_layout

